# CARL — Cursor rules (dogfooded seed)

The dogfooded final version is produced by running CARL on the CARL repo via
the Cursor adapter. This is the seed.

- Default model: composer-2 (cost). Switch to claude-opus-4-7 for diagnosis
  and reward-design touch-ups.
- Always run `pytest -q --strict-markers` before claiming a fix.
- Type-annotate all public functions; `mypy --strict` must pass.
- Never modify reward code from inside an episode unless the failure trace
  attributes failure to a reward-side bug.
- Every promoted diff must reference ≥ 2 pieces of trace evidence.
